# Task S55-T4: UI Proportions and Contrast

## Description
1. Improve contrast between blocks. Make sure independent elements are visually separated (add appropriate shadows, borders, or background tint).
2. The "black highlighted blocks" (possibly selected state or thick borders) should be made as thin as possible.
3. Reduce the size of the Date selection block. It currently takes up too much vertical space.
4. Make the Mileage/Distance info block below the date smaller (fit it strictly into single shorter line).
5. On the map screen, guarantee a 50/50 vertical division between the Map and the bottom panel (Date/Distance settings).

## Acceptance Criteria
- UI elements do not blend together awkwardly.
- Highlight borders are subtle (1px).
- The map covers at least 50% of the screen real-estate height.
- Date module is compact.
